metrics.title: Sales
metrics.tip: Sales = Gross Sales - Discounts + Taxes + Shipping (i.e. what the customer paid for shipping)

metrics.title: New Customer Revenue
metrics.tip: New Customer Revenue = Amount of Sales derived from New Customers

metrics.title: Net Sales
metrics.tip: Net Sales = Sales - Refunds (Note: Sales is as defined in our Sales metric)

metrics.title: Returning Customer Revenue
metrics.tip: Returning Customer Revenue = Amount of Sales derived from Returning Customers

metrics.title: Payment Gateways
metrics.tip: Payment Gateways = Payment processing fees. Edit these in: Store > Gateway Costs

metrics.title: COGS
metrics.tip: COGS = Cost of Goods Sold. Imported from Shopify, or edit these in: Store > Cost of Goods

metrics.title: Handling Fees
metrics.tip: Handling Fees = Cost of boxing, packaging, or “pick & pack” services. Edit these in: Store > Cost of Goods

metrics.title: Custom Expenses
metrics.tip: Custom Expenses = Any additional expenses you'd like to see deducted from your Net Profit. Edit these in: Store > Custom Expenses

metrics.title: Items
metrics.tip: Number of total items you have in stock.

metrics.title: Missing Items
metrics.tip: Missing Items = number of back order items.

metrics.title: Cost
metrics.tip: How much did the items cost.

metrics.title: Value
metrics.tip: Value = retail value of items in stock.

metrics.title: AOV
metrics.tip: AOV (Average Order Value) = Sales / Orders>$0

metrics.title: AOV
metrics.tip: Google Analytics reported average order value.

metrics.title: Facebook Ads
metrics.tip: Ads = ad spend.

metrics.title: Google Ads
metrics.tip: Ads = Google ad spend.

metrics.title: Google CPA
metrics.tip: CPA = cost per purchase.

metrics.title: Bounce Rate
metrics.tip: Bounce Rate = percentage of visitors to the website that leave before any action or visiting other pages.

metrics.title: Google Conversion Value
metrics.tip: Conversion Value = recorded revenue from Google ads.

metrics.title: Snapchat Ads
metrics.tip: Ads = Snapchat ad spend.

metrics.title: Snapchat ROAS
metrics.tip: ROAS = return on ad spend.

metrics.title: Conversion Rate
metrics.tip: Google Analytics reported conversion rate.

metrics.title: Net Profit
metrics.tip: Net Profit = Sales - Returns - Expenses (COGS, Shipping, Handling, Payment Gateways, Taxes, Custom Expenses) - Blended Ad Spend.

metrics.title: Cash Turnover
metrics.tip: Cash Turnover = Sales - Shipping - Taxes - Blended Ad Spend - Returns.

metrics.title: Net Margin
metrics.tip: Net Margin = Net Profit / Sales x 100. In other words: Percentage of Sales that is Net Profit. Answers the question of: “What percentage of my [Sales] is my [Net Profit]?”

metrics.title: Blended CPA
metrics.tip: Cost Per Acquisition is Ad spend/Google Analytics Transaction.

metrics.title: RPS
metrics.tip: RPS (Revenue Per Session) = Sales / Web Sessions.

metrics.title: Refunds
metrics.tip: Refunds = The amount refunded during the selected timeframe. Note that the refunded amount applies on the refund date, not on the original date of sale. Triple Whale may not match Shopify on a day-to-day basis.

metrics.title: Facebook ROAS
metrics.tip: ROAS = return on ad spend.

metrics.title: Google ROAS
metrics.tip: ROAS = return on ad spend.

metrics.title: Google CTR
metrics.tip: CTR = percentage of people clicking the ad.

metrics.title: Google CPM
metrics.tip: CPM = cost per 1000 impressions.

metrics.title: Google CPC
metrics.tip: CPC = cost per click.

metrics.title: Google All CPA
metrics.tip: All CPA = cost per all conversions.

metrics.title: Facebook CPC
metrics.tip: CPC = cost per click.

metrics.title: Facebook View Conversion Value
metrics.tip: VCV = Facebook View Conversion Value

metrics.title: Facebook View ROAS
metrics.tip: VROAS = Facebook View ROAS

metrics.title: Facebook View CPA
metrics.tip: VCPA = Facebook View CPA

metrics.title: Facebook CPM
metrics.tip: CPM = cost per 1000 impressions.

metrics.title: Facebook CTR
metrics.tip: CTR = percentage of people clicking the ad.

metrics.title: Facebook CPOC
metrics.tip: Cost Per Outbound Click.

metrics.title: Facebook Conversion Value
metrics.tip: Conversion Value = Facebook-reported revenue from Purchases on your site or on Meta Shop

metrics.title: Facebook Web Conversion Value
metrics.tip: Web Conversion Value = Facebook-reported revenue from Purchases on your site

metrics.title: Facebook Meta Conversion Value
metrics.tip: Meta Conversion Value = Facebook-reported revenue from Purchases on Meta Shop

metrics.title: Revenue Per Link Click
metrics.tip: Revenue per link click = Conversion value / Out bound clicks.

metrics.title: Facebook CPA
metrics.tip: CPA = cost per purchase (Approx).

metrics.title: Purchases
metrics.tip: Purchases - Orders made on your site or on Meta Shop

metrics.title: Meta Purchases
metrics.tip: Meta Purchases - Orders made on Meta Shop

metrics.title: Web Purchases
metrics.tip: Web Purchases - Orders made on your site

metrics.title: New Customers CPA
metrics.tip: NCPA (New Customer Cost Per Acquisition) = Total Ad Spend / New Customers.

metrics.title: Email Open Rate
metrics.tip: Email Open Rate = received emails / opened emails. On a one day view this metric is off and in general TripleWhale's number does not match Klaviyo's number.

metrics.title: CVR
metrics.tip: Purchase number / Received Emails

metrics.title: Revenue Per Email
metrics.tip: Sales / Received Emails

metrics.title: LTV
metrics.tip: LTV (Lifetime Value) = Sales / Unique Customers

metrics.title: Frequency
metrics.tip: Frequency = The average number of times Unique Customers place a purchase.

metrics.title: LTV/CPA
metrics.tip: LTV/CPA = Lifetime Value / Cost Per Acquisition

metrics.title: MER
metrics.tip: MER (Marketing Efficiency Ratio) = Percentage of Sales spent on Ads.

metrics.title: Returns %
metrics.tip: Returns % = Refunds / Sales. The percentage of your returns relative to your sales.

metrics.title: Orders
metrics.tip: Orders = Number of Orders within the selected timeframe

metrics.title: Taxes
metrics.tip: Taxes = Amount customers paid in taxes (not including shipping taxes).

metrics.title: New Customers
metrics.tip: New Customers = Percentage of orders placed by New Customers

metrics.title: Returning Customers
metrics.tip: Returning Customers = Percentage of orders placed by Returning Customers

metrics.title: New Customer Orders
metrics.tip: New Customers = Number of orders placed by New Customers

metrics.title: Unique Customers
metrics.tip: Unique Customers = Number of Unique Customers within the selected timeframe

metrics.title: Shipping
metrics.tip: Shipping = Amount the store paid in shipping costs for fulfilling orders within the select timeframe. Edit these in: Store > Shipping

metrics.title: Items Sold
metrics.tip: Items Sold = Number of items sold within the selected timeframe

metrics.title: Blended Ad Spend
metrics.tip: Blended Ad Spend = Total Ad Spend. This includes the reported ad spend of each marketing channel connected to Triple Whale, plus any Custom Expenses marked as Ad Spend.

metrics.title: Blended ROAS
metrics.tip: Blended ROAS (Return on Ad Spend) = Sales / Blended Ads.

metrics.title: New Customer ROAS
metrics.tip: New Customer ROAS (Return on Ad Spend) = Sales from New Customers / Blended Ad Spend.

metrics.title: Blended Attributed ROAS
metrics.tip: BA ROAS (Blended-Attributed ROAS) = Total Blended Conversion Value (reported by each marketing channel) / Blended Ad Spend

metrics.title: Profit on Ad Spend
metrics.tip: POAS is Gross-Profit/Total-Ad-spend.

metrics.title: Blended CPA
metrics.tip: CPA (Cost Per Acquisition) = Blended Ad Spend / Orders > $0

metrics.title: Finance Cash Total
metrics.tip: The total amount of cash across all your business bank accounts at the end of this time period.

metrics.title: Finance Credit Total
metrics.tip: The total outstanding balance across all your business credit cards at the end of this time period.

metrics.title: Money In
metrics.tip: The total amount of cash that came into your business bank account(s) during this time period.

metrics.title: Money Out
metrics.tip: The total amount of cash that left your business bank account(s) during this time period.

metrics.title: Beginning Cash
metrics.tip: The total amount of cash you had in your business bank account(s) at the end of this time period.

metrics.title: Ending Cash
metrics.tip: The total amount of cash you had in your business bank account(s) at the beginning of this time period.

metrics.title: Total Change
metrics.tip: The difference between the amount of cash you had in your business bank account(s) at the beginning and end of this period.

metrics.title: Cost of Inventory in Stock
metrics.tip: Cost of Units in Stock

metrics.title: Value of Inventory in Stock
metrics.tip: Value of Units in Stock

metrics.title: Cash
metrics.tip: The total amount of cash you had in your business bank account(s) at the end of this time period.

metrics.title: Credit Card Debt
metrics.tip: The total amount of credit card debt you had at the end of this time period.

metrics.title: Invoices Total
metrics.tip: This represents the total amount that you need to pay across all your invoices.

metrics.title: Total Due within 30 Days
metrics.tip: This represents the total amount that you need to pay across all your invoices between now and 30 days from now.

metrics.title: Total Due within 60 Days
metrics.tip: This represents the total amount that you need to pay across all your invoices between now and 60 days from now.

metrics.title: Total Due within 90 Days
metrics.tip: This represents the total amount that you need to pay across all your invoices between now and 90 days from now.

metrics.title: EBITDA
metrics.tip: Earnings before interest, taxes, depreciation and amortization.

metrics.title: Burn Rate
metrics.tip: The amount of money your business lost during this time period, net of all expenses

metrics.title: Runway (Days)
metrics.tip: The amount of time you have before your business run out of cash (assuming no change in funding or business performance).

metrics.title: Valuation
metrics.tip: The value of your business.  Click this tile to edit the formula for valuation.

metrics.title: Average Daily Sales
metrics.tip: The amount of revenue your business generates on a typical day.

metrics.title: Invoices Total
metrics.tip: This represents the total amount that you need to pay across all your invoices
